<title>UK: C&amp;W Communications to be separately listed.</title>
<headline>C&amp;W Communications to be separately listed.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Cable &amp; Wireless Communications Plc will be listed separately following the completion of the planned merger of C&amp;W Plc's UK interests with those of NYNEX and Bell Canada, C&amp;W chief executive Richard H Brown told Reuters.  </p>
<p>In an interview, Brown said the company would be listed in New York and London, probably in about six months, assuming the completion of the cable merger that was announced earlier today.</p>
<p>C&amp;W deputy group chief executive Rod Olsen said about 15 percent of C&amp;W Communications would initialy be floated, a total which he said had been approved by the stock exchanges involved.</p>
